column5: So this is my first report and unfortunately its a short one for now. With the upcoming wedding (8 days), a 9 month old baby, and a full-time job, finding time to fish is difficult...but i do still manage to get out  Here are a couple nice smallies that i've gotten in the last couple weeks               thanks for the look!  Sam
Nice Smallies is an understatement   That first one is a BIG smallie  Thanks, and congrats on the wedding
wow that is one long bass! Would be even bigger come fall!  Cheers!
Very Nice Indeed! Are you going fishing on your honeymoon? I did.
I've heard of fishing the weeds before, but man .... that's thick cover.
very Nice.... congrats on the wedding too..  Splashhopper ( london )

thanks for the comments and congrats on the wedding guys ill definitely be doing some fishing on the honeymoon - whenever we get the time to take one  craig - im on shore there, the weeds are about 3 feet or so but they thin out at the water and you're able to cast comfortably

I didn't even see a boat!  We are all just messing.  But hey, that's a heck of a spot to try and pull a 'hog' out of.  Congrats on the wedding and things can wait, just not too long or she will take away your right to fish...
haha i figured as much, just wanted to describe the area im lucky though, my future wife loves to fish and joins me regularly
